Package: ddfr
Title: Work with discrete distributions with finite support in R
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(
      "fdf",
      email = "171835561+fdf-uni@users.noreply.github.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: This package enables you to create objects for representing
    discrete distributions with finite support by specifying their probability
    mass functions. These objects can then be used for a variety of tasks, from
    simple statistical analyses over plotting to convolutions.
